    All Classes and Interfaces

    Class
    Description
    ArcherTower
    The bread-and-butter defensive structure.
    BaseElement
    Represents a static, destructible object on the map (flower).
    BaseEnemy
    The fundamental class for all enemies.
    BaseEntity
    The grandfather of all objects in the game world.
    BaseTower
    The abstract engine for all defensive structures.
    BossEnemy
     
    BossWitchEnemy
     
    Bullet
    Represents a projectile fired by a tower.
    CellPane
    Represents a single tile/grid cell on the game map.
    EasyButton
    A custom-styled button for selecting the "Easy" difficulty.
    ElementI
    A basic map obstacle (Flower Type 1).
    ElementII
     
    ElementIII
     
    FastEnemy
     
    FastWitchEnemy
     
    FireTower
    Area of Effect (AoE) specialist.
    GameCanvas
    The main game container.
    GameController
    The central "God Object" or Facade that orchestrates the entire game state.
    GameOverPanel
    A modal panel displayed when the game ends (Win or Lose).
    GameSetting
    The central configuration class for the game.
    GhostTowerPreview
    A dedicated Canvas for drawing the tower placement preview.
    HardButton
    A custom-styled button for selecting the "Hard" difficulty.
    IceTower
    Utility tower that applies a Slow effect.
    InGameMenu
    The pause menu overlay displayed when the game is paused.
    IUpgradeable
    Contract for any game entity (usually Towers) that supports a leveling system.
    LaserTower
    High-speed, single-target damage dealer.
    Location
    Simple POJO to store Grid coordinates (Row, Column).
    Main
    The Main class serves as the entry point for the Cat Defense application.
    MainBase
    Represents the player's Headquarters/Base.
    MainMenu
    The main entry screen of the application.
    Map
    The visual representation of the game grid.
    MapLoader
    Static utility class for loading map data and calculating the enemy path.
    MoneyText
    HUD element displaying the player's current money.

    NormalWitchEnemy

    TowerManager
    Factory class for creating Tower instances.
    TowerSelector
    The bottom toolbar allowing players to select which tower to build.
    UpgradePanel
    A floating UI panel that appears when a user clicks on an existing tower.
    Wave
    Data Object (POJO) representing a single wave of enemies.
    WaveLoader
    Factory class responsible for generating the sequence of Waves.
    WaveManager
    Manages the progression of game waves and the timing of enemy spawns.
    WaveText
    HUD element displaying the current wave number.
